## Build & run

{% if build_tool == "maven" %}
```bash
# Build + run tests
./mvnw verify

# Run the app locally (dev profile)
./mvnw spring-boot:run -Dspring-boot.run.profiles=dev
{% else %}
```bash
# Build + run tests
./gradlew build

# Run the app locally (dev profile)
./gradlew bootRun --args='--spring.profiles.active=dev'
{% endif %}

# Run the packaged JAR
java -jar target/{{ artifact_id }}-*.jar --spring.profiles.active=dev
```

The service starts on `http://localhost:8080`.

{% if has_actuator %}
Health check: `GET http://localhost:8080/actuator/health`
{% else %}
Health check: `GET http://localhost:8080/api/health`
{% endif %}

## Configuration

{% if "config-profiles" in extras %}
Profiles are split into `application-dev.yml` and `application-prod.yml`:

- `dev` — local defaults (H2 / local DB, verbose logging)
- `prod` — reads sensitive values from environment variables

Activate with `SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=prod` or `--spring.profiles.active=prod`.
{% else %}
Configuration lives in `src/main/resources/application.properties`.
{% endif %}

